definitions.name: fail
definitions.description: Display the explanatory message and then terminate the program

definitions.name: logger
definitions.description: Get a logger for the specified topic.

definitions.name: Buffer
definitions.description: A stateless buffer of bytes. Default byte order is network byte order.

definitions.name: getByte
definitions.description: read a byte at the specified index

definitions.name: putByte
definitions.description: write a byte at the specified index

definitions.name: getShort
definitions.description: read a short at the specified index

definitions.name: putShort
definitions.description: write a short at the specified index

definitions.name: getInt
definitions.description: read an int at the specified index

definitions.name: putInt
definitions.description: write an int at the specified index

definitions.name: getLong
definitions.description: read a long at the specified index

definitions.name: putLong
definitions.description: write a long at the specified index

definitions.name: getFloat
definitions.description: read a float at the specified index

definitions.name: putFloat
definitions.description: write a float at the specified index

definitions.name: getStringUTF8
definitions.description: decode length bytes as a UTF8 string at the specified index

definitions.name: putStringUTF8
definitions.description: write a string encoded in UTF8 at the specified index and return encoded length

definitions.name: getSlice
definitions.description: get a view of the range

definitions.name: putSlice
definitions.description: copy length bytes from the source buffer starting at offset to the specified index

definitions.name: littleEndian
definitions.description: get a littleEndian view of the same buffer

definitions.name: isNetworkByteOrder
definitions.description: true if the buffer decodes in network byte order

definitions.name: Codec
definitions.description: Various String and Buffer conversion routines

definitions.name: buffer
definitions.description: Create an empty buffer with the specified capacity

definitions.name: toHexdump
definitions.description: Encode the specified slice of the buffer and insert a space every 2^spaceScale bytes

definitions.name: fromHexdump
definitions.description: decode the hexdump ignoring leading 0x and any intervening spaces

definitions.name: toBase64
definitions.description: Encode the specified slice of the buffer as Base64

definitions.name: Appender
definitions.description: Destination for logging, just a marker interface for now

definitions.name: setAppender
definitions.description: Set the destination for logging, default stderr()

definitions.name: trace
definitions.description: emit a log at trace level

definitions.name: debug
definitions.description: emit a log at debug level

definitions.name: info
definitions.description: emit a log at info level

definitions.name: warn
definitions.description: emit a log at warn level

definitions.name: error
definitions.description: emit a log at error level

definitions.name: toJSON
definitions.description: Serializes object tree into JSON. skips over fields starting with underscore

definitions.name: fromJSON
definitions.description: deserialize json into provided result object. Skip over fields starting with underscore

definitions.name: Servlet
definitions.description: A service addresable with an url

definitions.name: onServletInit
definitions.description: called after the servlet is successfully installed. The url will be the actual url used, important especially if ephemeral port was requested

definitions.name: onServletError
definitions.description: called if the servlet could not be installed

definitions.name: onServletEnd
definitions.description: called when the servlet is removed

definitions.name: DegenerateResolver
definitions.description: DegenerateResolver assumes that the serviceName is an URL.

definitions.name: Event
definitions.description: The contract between event implementations and Collector

definitions.name: FutureListener
definitions.description: event handler for a future completion

definitions.name: FutureCompletion
definitions.description: internal class that binds a listener to a future

definitions.name: EventContext
definitions.description: Captures the current context, base class for all event source implementations

definitions.name: Future
definitions.description: The base class for value objects

definitions.name: CollectorExecutor
definitions.description: Fire events one by one with no locks held

definitions.name: Collector
definitions.description: An active queue of events. Each event will fire sequentially, one by one. Multiple instances of Collector are not serialized with eachother and may run in parallel.

definitions.name: Context
definitions.description: The logical stack for async stuff.

definitions.name: onHTTPRequest
definitions.description: incoming request. respond with Runtime.respond(). After responding the objects may get recycled by the runtime

definitions.name: onWSConnect
definitions.description: called for each new incoming WebSocket connection
